  <front>
    <title>Minimal EDNS compliance requirements</title>
    <seriesInfo name="Internet-Draft" value="draft-spacek-edns-camel-diet-01"/>
    <author initials="P." surname="Špaček" fullname="Petr Špaček"/>
    <author initials="O." surname="Guðmundsson" fullname="Ólafur Guðmundsson"/>
    <author initials="O." surname="Surý" fullname="Ondřej Surý"/>
    <date day="29" month="May" year="2018"></date>
    <abstract>
      <t>   DNS responders must either follow RFC 6891 by fully implementing EDNS
   or at least respond to queries containing OPT record according to
   older specifications.  Non-compliant implementations which do not
   respond at all are not worth talking to.

	 </t>
    </abstract>
  </front>
